---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title='Terms and Conditions'>
  <section
    class='terms-and-conditions py-20 bg-gradient-to-b from-blue-50 to-white'
  >
    <div
      class='container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-3xl rounded-2xl shadow-xl bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-md'
    >
      <h1
        class='text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-primary mb-4 text-center'
      >
        Terms and Conditions
      </h1>
      <h2
        class='text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-8 text-center'
      >
        Thank you for choosing Mendonca's Global Gateway!<br />By using our
        services, you agree to the following terms and conditions:
      </h2>

      <div class='space-y-8'>
        <div>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-2'>
            1. Service Overview
          </h3>
          <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
            <li>
              We provide a seamless service for importing goods from the U.S. to
              Guyana.
            </li>
            <li>
              Our partner, Guyana Freight Services Inc., manages the U.S.-based
              warehouse, customs clearance, and local delivery in Guyana.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-2'>
            2. Responsibilities of Customers
          </h3>
          <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
            <li>
              Ensure all items purchased comply with Guyana's import
              regulations.
            </li>
            <li>
              Provide accurate and complete information when signing up or
              placing orders.
            </li>
            <li>
              Pay all applicable fees (freight handling and VAT) upon arrival of
              your package in Guyana.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-2'>
            3. Shipping Schedule
          </h3>
          <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
            <li>
              Packages are shipped from the U.S. on Mondays and Thursdays.
            </li>
            <li>Customs clearance occurs on Tuesdays and Fridays.</li>
            <li>
              Delivery to your address in Guyana typically takes 1–2 business
              days after clearance.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-2'>
            4. Costs and Payments
          </h3>
          <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
            <li>You are responsible for paying:</li>
            <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
              <li>
                Freight Handling: Based on the weight/volume of your package.
              </li>
              <li>
                VAT: Calculated according to Guyana Revenue Authority (GRA)
                guidelines.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <li>
              Payments must be made before your package is released for
              delivery.
            </li>
            <li>
              Payments can be made at the current exchange rate of $222 GYD/USD, or in cash/MMG at drop-off.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-2'>
            5. Storage Policy
          </h3>
          <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
            <li>
              Upon invoicing, customers have 4 days to collect packages.
            </li>
            <li>
              From Day 5 onwards, storage fees of $500 GYD per day will apply.
            </li>
            <li>
              We recommend collecting your packages promptly to avoid additional storage fees.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-2'>
            6. Prohibited Items
          </h3>
          <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
            <li>Hazardous materials (e.g., chemicals, weapons)</li>
            <li>
              Perishable goods (unless refrigerated shipping becomes available)
            </li>
            <li>Illegal or counterfeit items</li>
            <li>Any item restricted by Guyana customs laws</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-2'>7. Liability</h3>
          <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
            <li>
              We are not liable for delays caused by customs inspections, public
              holidays, or unforeseen circumstances.
            </li>
            <li>
              While we take every precaution to ensure safe delivery, we are not
              responsible for damage or loss caused by third-party carriers or
              natural disasters.
            </li>
            <li>
              For lost or damaged items, claims must be submitted within 7 days
              of delivery.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class='text-xl font-bold text-secondary mb-2'>
            8. Refunds and Returns
          </h3>
          <ul class='list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700'>
            <li>
              Refunds are not issued for services rendered unless there is a
              proven error on our part.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
